main event: An unidentified object was tracked on radar and visually observed by a military aircraft over Okinawa on February 7, 1953.
interesting points: The object was visually tracked for approximately 15 minutes by radar before a military interceptor was scrambled,The F-94 made visual contact with a bright orange colored object that changed in size and shape,The incident occurred under scattered stratus cloud conditions,The conclusion indicated that the object was probably Venus, which is known as the 'evening star',The sighting was classified as unclassified after investigation.
witness description: visual contact made by military personnel in an F-94 aircraft
